2:T4e6,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Can AI marketing agents replace a marketing team?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"AI marketing agents excel at execution tasks — writing drafts, scheduling posts, adjusting bids, generating reports. They work best as force multipliers for human marketers who set strategy, review outputs, and handle creative direction. Most teams use them to scale output, not eliminate headcount."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Will AI-generated content hurt my SEO?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Google evaluates content quality, not authorship. AI-generated content that is accurate, well-structured, and genuinely useful for readers performs well in search. Thin, generic, or duplicate AI content performs poorly — just as human-written thin content does."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the difference between an AI marketing agent and a tool like Jasper?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Tools like Jasper are AI writing assistants — they help humans write content faster. AI marketing agents are autonomous — they can plan, create, publish, and optimise content or campaigns with minimal human input at each step."}}]}5:["slug","what-is-an-ai-marketing-agent","d"]
